I don't have any particularly elegant solution to these types of problem right now, but it should be possible to implement as follows:

For any control that modifies the forms fields, you can either 1) add an action to the field that will be called on the view controller and tell it to reload the form, or a subset of the form (the action can be either a block or a selector to call on the view controller), or 2) add a KVO observer on the form itself that does the same.

The fields method of the form is called whenever the formController.forms property is set, so as an example, your switch action could do this:

```
- (void)allDaySwitchAction
{
    //reload form fields
    self.formController.form = self.formController.form;

    //reload table
    [self.formController.tableView reloadData];
}
```

Then, in the fields method of your form, return a different configuration depending on the value of the allDay property.

If you can think of a better way to do this, please let me know.

