This isn't a bug, but I can see why it's confusing.

The values returned by the form has nothing to do with the enum, it's just the index of the option you select. Enums have no runtime representation - they're just a convenient way of representing constants, but there's no way for FXForms to know what values you've used.

If you want non-zero-based, non-sequential option values, you can specify that actual numbers as your FXFormFieldOptions and then use a valueTransformer to convert them to strings, like this:

```
{FXFormFieldOptions: @[@(GenderMale), @(GenderFemale), @(GenderOther)],
 FXFormFieldValueTransformer: ^(id input) {
        return @{@(GenderMale): @"Male",
                       @(GenderFemale): @"Female",
                       @(GenderOther): @"Other"}[input];
 }};
```

